;Description
:This template is used to create a basic navigation box at the bottom of the page.  In theory, it is supposed to be [sarcasm] obvious [/s] how to use it.  In practice, the letter-V is used to '''View''' each sub-navbox (sorta similar to SHOW); while the letter-E is used to '''Edit''' that same sub-navbox.

:Also on the right-hand-side, the words '''Show''' and '''Hide''' are toggles to display the ''contents'' of the main and sub-navboxes, in situ.  However, if you click on the '''View''' item - you will be transported over to the exact sub-navbox you chose.  (nb: View and Show for the main top-level navbox are equivalent)

:The sub-navboxes themselves are designed to only show ''LINKS'' to other articles or pages.  Thus, as new pages get added to the wikia; it is supposed to be [sarcasm] easy [/s] to add them to the navigation menus in their appropriate places.

:see also: [[Wikipedia:Template:Navbox]]
;Syntax
:Type <code>{{t|navbox}}</code> at the end of the page to get this item transcluded (no parameters)

;Sample output

<pre>{{navbox}}</pre>

Results in...

{{navbox}}

<hr/>

;Sample output for each individual sub-Navbox

<pre>{{Characters_Navbox}}<hr/>
{{Starships_Navbox}}<hr/>
{{Tiers_Navbox}}<hr/>
{{Menus_Navbox}}<hr/>
</pre>

Results in...

{{Characters_Navbox}}<hr/>
{{Starships_Navbox}}<hr/>
{{Tiers_Navbox}}<hr/>
{{Menus_Navbox}}<hr/>

